Convex Clustering Using Random Effects

The code is modified and it can give some “meaningful” clustering, but the strange behaviour when \(\gamma\) small retains from the previous section (could still be coding ERRORS).

The following two animations show the clustering of the same dataset using just the random effects (penalizing \(\beta\)’s) and using the predicted values at 10%, 20%, …, 90% quantiles of pooled sampled times, respectively.
